thread.title_full: P.B. Gardens overruns Jupiter for district win - Sun Sentinel

author: Steve Dorsey
title: P.B. Gardens overruns Jupiter for district win
text:
Palm Beach Gardens used a punishing rushing attack en route to a 21-3 win over district rival Jupiter on Friday night.
The victory puts Gardens (3-2) at 2-0 in District 9-8A play and helped soothe the pain of a thumping from rival Dwyer last week. Jupiter drops to 0-5 on the season.
Palm Beach Gardens pounded Jupiter's defense for 210 yards rushing. Senior Donnell Perry was the workhorse in the backfield for the Gators, tallying 110 yards on 23 carries. His 4-yard touchdown run early in the fourth quarter accounted for the final score.
Senior quarterback Hunter Aranda notched Gardens' other two touchdowns, both on 1-yard sneaks.
"It probably wasn't pretty. We decided we were going to run the ball from the get-go," Gardens coach Rob Freeman said.
Palm Beach Gardens marched 94 yards on its second possession and grabbed a 7-0 lead with Aranda's first sneak. The quarterback also scored on a short sneak early in the third quarter after Gardens blocked a Jupiter punt that gave the Gators possession at the Warriors' 14.

Palm Beach Gardens had a chance to extend its lead just before halftime but the drive stalled at the 6 when time expired, and the Gators went to the locker room clinging to a 7-3 lead.
